# Coding Style Guidelines

## Code Quality Standards
- Follow PEP 8 guidelines
- Fix all linter warnings
- Maintain consistent style across the codebase
- Use type hints for all function parameters and return values
- Keep functions focused and single-purpose
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add docstrings to all public functions and classes

## Code Organization
- Keep imports organized and grouped
- Use absolute imports
- Group related functionality in modules
- Keep files focused on a single responsibility
- Use appropriate abstraction levels

## Documentation
- Update docstrings for all code changes
- Add inline comments for complex logic
- Keep comments current and relevant
- Document any non-obvious decisions
- Include examples in docstrings where helpful

## Logging
- Add appropriate log levels
- Include relevant context in log messages
- Use consistent log message format
- Log important state changes
- Include error details in exception logs 